[[File:Steel armour set (lg) equipped.png|thumb|130px|A player with steel armour equipped.]]
'''Steel equipment''' are items made from [[Metal#Basic metals|steel metal]]. Steel equipment is stronger than [[iron equipment]], but weaker than [[black equipment]]. All steel items are coloured light-grey. Steel armour requires 5 [[Defence]] to wield, weapons require 5 [[Attack]].

==Weapons==
'''Steel weapons''' require an [[Attack]] level of 5 to wield.

===One-handed melee weapons===
{{Infotable Bonuses|Steel dagger#(unp)|Steel axe|Steel mace|Steel sword|Steel longsword|Steel scimitar|Steel hasta#(unp)|Steel warhammer|Steel battleaxe|Steel pickaxe|sort=str|nototals=yes}}

===Two-handed melee weapons===
{{Infotable Bonuses|Steel claws|Steel spear#(unp)|Steel 2h sword|Steel halberd|sort=str|nototals=yes}}

===Ranged weapons and ammo===
{{Infotable Bonuses|Steel crossbow|Steel bolts#Unpoisoned|Steel arrow#(unp)|Steel brutal|Steel dart#(unp)|Steel javelin#Unpoisoned|Steel thrownaxe|Steel knife#(unp)|sort=rstr|nototals=yes}}

==Armour==
'''Steel armour''' is the third-lowest quality [[armour]] in the standard spectrum of metal armours ([[Bronze equipment#Armour|bronze]] to [[Dragon equipment#Armour|dragon]]). Steel armour requires 5 [[Defence]] to wear.

{{Infotable Bonuses|Steel med helm|Steel full helm|Steel chainbody|Steel platebody|Steel platelegs|Steel plateskirt|Steel sq shield|Steel kiteshield|Steel boots|Steel gloves|Steel defender#Normal|sort=dslash|nototals=yes}}

==Other==
[[Steel trimmed armour|Trimmed]] and [[Steel gold-trimmed armour|gold-trimmed]] steel armour have the same bonuses as standard steel armour. These can be obtained from the member's only [[Treasure Trails]] minigame.

'''Note:''' Other players '''''cannot''''' trim or bless armour. Players claiming to do so are scammers.

